what kind of fish should i put in my gallon aquarium i already have a creamsicle platy and a red wag platy also will a bala shark be ok or is it to agressive no bala sharks they grow to be and need to be in at least a gallon tank find out what gender of platies you have here is a site that should help with sexing http sogua mamakcorner com uploads platy sexing jpg also here is a pic of a male platy http www dpi qld gov au images gif http www fishforever co uk images male jpg here is a pic of female http www dpi qld gov au images gif http www fishforever co uk images female jpg if you have males then just leave them if you have male and female get more female platy if you have females then just leave them the only reason to get more female is so the male won't harass the female you currenlty have as far as other fish i would get a small group of panda or pygmy corydoras catfish they will do a nice job eating left over fish food but do need more to their diet shrimp pellets are a nice diet for them they have them at wal mart for about bucks for a huge can here is a pic of the panda http www putzderblitz at aquaristik aquaristik ccweb dscn jpg here is a pic of a pygmy http www aquahobby com gallery e pygmaeus php the pandas are easier to find usually and cheaper then the pygmy i would also add a male betta usually they will get along with other fish fine especially if the tank wasn't theirs first be sure to have lots of hiding spaces though hope this helps good luck Tilapia Fishing Clownfish Dwarf gourami Giant Panda HyperText Transfer Protocol Live-bearing aquarium fish Shark Patricia Ford JPEG Sea-Monkey Wallpaper group Sailfin Molly World Wide Web Vegetarianism Biodiesel Grasshopper Catfish Salmon Fish farming Common Unix Printing System Seahorse Gar Gallery of sovereign state coats of arms Fauna of Australia Georgia Aquarium Domestic goat Southern platyfish Hydrogen economy Corydoras Representational State Transfer Fish Domestic rabbit Marine aquarium Green swordta